Patient is a known asthmatic and on  bronchodilator treatment since 6 yrs, H/O Diabetes present and on oral Hypoglycemic drugs. She is having deflected nasal septum towards left side with multiple grayish white masses appear as grapes in the middle meatus of both the nostrils, insensitive to touch and don’t bleed.
